{{Infobox university | name = Faculty of Political Science in Sarajevo | native_name = Fakultet političkih nauka u Sarajevu | image_size = | image_alt = | caption = Seal of the Faculty of Political Science in Sarajevo | latin_name = | motto = | motto_lang = | mottoeng = | established = 1961 | closed = | type = [[Faculty (division)|Faculty]] | affiliation = | endowment = | budget = | rector = | officer_in_charge = | chairman = | chancellor = | president = | vice-president = | superintendent = | provost = | vice_chancellor = | principal = | dean = Šaćir Filandra | director = | head_label = | head = | academic_staff = | administrative_staff = | students = | undergrad = | postgrad = | doctoral = | other = | city = [[Sarajevo]] | state = | province = [[Sarajevo Canton]] | country = [[Bosnia and Herzegovina]] | campus = [[urban area|Urban]] | former_names = Visoka škola političkih nauka Sarajevo | free_label = | free = | athletics = | colours = | sports = | nickname = FPN or FPN Sarajevo | mascot = | website = {{URL|www.fpn.unsa.ba}} | logo = | footnotes = | image_name = Logo of Faculty of Political Science in Sarajevo.png | coor = | colors =Turquoise | affiliations = [[University of Sarajevo]] }}
The '''Faculty of Political Science in Sarajevo''' ({{lang-bs|Fakultet političkih nauka u Sarajevu}}) or '''FPN''' is one of the 24. [[Faculty (division)|faculties]] of [[University of Sarajevo]]. The faculty was formed in 1961. as former "High School of Political Science in Sarajevo" and it is located in [[urban area]] of [[Sarajevo]] (between [[Drvenija Bridge]] and [[Čobanija Bridge]]).<ref name="History of the Faculty">{{cite news|title = Historijat|date=2013-05-29|author=FPN Sarajevo|page=http://www.fpn.unsa.ba/ba/historijat/|language=Bosnian}}</ref> Faculty actively participates in the [[Bologna Process]] in [[Bosnia and Herzegovina]], publishes scholarly papers, review articles, research notes and book reviews covering major areas of political sciences, sociology, security studies, social work, and [[media studies]]. [[Sarajevo Social Science Review]] has been published by the Faculty of Political Sciences Sarajevo (formerly ''Godišnjak Fakulteta političkih nauka'' - ''Annual Papers of Faculty of Political Sciences''). There is also FPN [[student newspaper]]s called ''SPONA''.
==Organization== The Faculty of Political Science in Sarajevo has five departments and one institute: *Department of [[Politology]] *Department of [[Sociology]] *Department of [[Communication studies]] ([[Journalism]]) *Department of [[Social work]] *Department of [[Security]] and [[Peace studies]] *Institute of [[Social Research]]
==Degree programs== Educational process at the Faculty of Political Sciences is carried out in three cycles of study: *The Bachelor's program (BA) lasts three years carrying 180 [[European Credit Transfer and Accumulation System|ECTS]] credits *The Master's program (MA) lasts two years carrying 120 [[European Credit Transfer and Accumulation System|ECTS]] credits *The Doctoral program (PhD) lasts three years carrying 180 [[European Credit Transfer and Accumulation System|ECTS]] credits
